data.description: Explore the house hacking opportunity of a lifetime with this exceptional 1886 Queen Anne Victorian near Cheesman Park. Boasting annual short-term rental income of around $60k from a private garden-level apartment, the main residence spans 3 floors, seamlessly blending luxury & historical charm. Original trim work & two fireplaces on the main floor offer an incredible space to entertain. The family room, adorned with a bay window, offers a tranquil space for reading or morning coffee with views of the tree-lined street. The professional chef's kitchen is incredible, equipped with a Kenmore professional fridge, Viking dishwasher, drawer microwave, Viking 6-burner stove, oven, & Zephyr hood vent. Choose between the main staircase, with the exquisite Restoration Hardware Chandelier, or the aux staircase to access the 2nd floor. Here, the primary bedroom features a custom walk-in shower with 4 jets & several shower heads. Two additional bedrooms share a recently refinished clawfoot bathtub & custom vanity. French doors lead to a deck with stunning Denver skyline views. Ascend to the 3rd floor to find a bedroom, office nook, & media room with a loft large tv area and bar. The rear patio with an established grapevine is great for entertaining or relaxation. Past the 2.5-car garage with Tesla charger is a turf yard, perfect for kids or pets. Navigate through the front gardens to access the fully furnished private garden-level apartment. Generating significant income, this space can continue as a short-term rental, accommodate multi-gen living, an Au Pair, or long term tenancy. Explore zoning possibilities for adding a 3rd unit, enhancing income potential. Preliminary plans for a carriage house atop the garage are available. Please note that these plans haven't been reviewed by city planning, an architect, or structural engineer. Seize this unique chance to reside in a luxurious historic home in the heart of Cheesman Park. Listing agent has ownership interest in the home.
